National Chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC) Abdullahi Adamu has told the Ekiti State governorship campaign council to deliver the state in the June 18 election. The chairman spoke while inaugurating the 61-man governorship campaign council at the national secretariat in Abuja. The committee is chaired by Kebi State Governor Atiku Bagudu. Adamu urged the members to work to the best of their abilities to deliver the party’s mandate.   ‘I will sign law establishing Fraud institute’     Navy marks 66th anniversary     CNPP urges Buhari to sack ministers   He said: “I have one thing in the marching order of this party, and that is don’t come home crying. If there’s crying, let them go, let them go and cry for their principals, not us. “Ekiti is the first election that we will be having in this dispensation of APC. God has blessed our lives; God has blessed my life and my political career. Once there’s a contest, there will be a winner and a loser but we are never on the losing side. “We will work as hard as we can to ensure that we deliver our candidate as the next governor of Ekiti State,” Adamu added. Bagudu, on behalf of the committee, thanked the party for the opportunity given to them and expressed optimism to deliver on their part.